      "content": "the pretending is the worst part. it's like i'm carrying around this heavy weight of being a person, but there's no one actually home. it feels so pointless to just keep dragging this empty shell through the years when the person who actually mattered is long gone. it feels like i'm just occupying space that doesn't belong to me anymore.",
